values:
I'm in a bad mood today.  The focus is in the shop and the repairs are going to be over 500 bucks.  That comes in perfect time for christmas and the cruise.  It's a good thing I don't have anything in my bank account right now.  Time to rack up the ole credit card once again.  

p.s. Don't buy a ford.
It's nice to smile again.  Now if i could just fix that one thing life would be a lot easier.
I'm finially learning that I don't have to live my life according to a plan.  It's ok to live day by day.  Let's see what happens.  Maybe it will be fun.  I'm not as scared as I used to be.
i'm starting to feel alive and happy again.

I don't really know how to put my emotions into words.  I guess all i can say is that lately I have been confused as usual.  I have also been really depressed and scared.  I don't know where my life is heading, and I lost a really good friend in the process of trying to figure shit out.  Everyone tells me that these things happen and that they are a part of life.  Friendships come and go I guess but hearing that doesn't make it any easier.  I'm really tore up about it to be honest.  Anyways I gotta get ready for work.  I hope everyone is enjoying the holiday weekend.  Luv ya guys.
I will be having a graduation party on July 23rd.  That is on a saturday.  It will be going on all day and all night. I would love to see everyone there if you can make it.

Yesterday I went down to the taste fest.  I was so excited to see straylight run and coheed and cambria.  Of course my sister had a crisis when she went swimming and her hair turned green (again).  So she decided that she needed my car to go to the solon.  She told me she had it worked out that when my mom got home I could take her car to the solon then I could switch cars with Erica there on my way to pick up Shannon and Karen.  Then of course when my mom got home she didn't have gas in her car.  So I had to go to the bank and draw money to put gas in her car to drive to the solon only to find out that Erica didn't put any gas in my car like she had promised.  At this point I was already kind of running late so I was pissed off.  When I picked up Shannon and Karen and got downtown I had calmed down.  I looked at the clock and I wasn't late.  So we found the 89x stage only to find out that the shows had been canceled due to flight delays.  Man I was pissed for a few mins.  Then I reminded myself that I hadn't bought tickets or anything and that I should just make the best of it.  So that is what I did, I made the best of it.  I spent the rest of the evening with two really awesome girls and we drank margaritas.  It was a lot of fun.  We got to sample some awesome food and we listened to some good music.  The highlight of the night I think was Karen left her purse in the port o potty.  She went back and looked in each potty.  The one that had her purse in it also had a guy peeing, but that didn't seem to phase Karen.  She just opened the door and grabbed her purse while the dude was peeing.  It gave Shannon and I a good chuckle. It was a good time.
Got the job at beaumont finally.  Finally i will have some structure to my life once again.  Maybe now i will be able to piece things back together in my life.
Ok things can start making sense already.
Trying to make sense of my life.  Anyone care to help?

Tilly and the wall - I always Knew
I am starting a new chapter in my life.

I still haven't started working yet.  I need some cash so i really should get on that.  I know what i have to do but i'm afraid to do it.  I have never been very good at dealing with change.  Anyone that really knows me will agree with that.  I know it's time to grow up now though.  I can't run from things, or close my eyes and wish them away.  I also need to accept that no matter how much i wish for it that there is no such thing as a rewind button when it comes to real life.  I guess i have problems understanding how life can become so complex when all that I really want seems so simple.  I want happiness for myself and for the people I care about.  But somewhere in all of that things just get so confusing.  Drama comes into your life when you are unprepared to deal with it.  The people you care about you just can't seem to make happy, in fact you end up contributing to their missery.  It's as if the simple things in life come with the highest price tag.  Maybe they are not that simple afterall.  Maybe my brain is telling myself lies.  It seems like life should be simple.  My perspective must be flawed.  A friend of mine told me that there is beauty in the struggles of life.  I'm sure that is probably true because it seems like with most struggles there is an element of love in it, and love is beautiful.  I just wish that the love could shine brighter to help guide us through these sturggles.  Maybe if love shined brighter then I could see the beauty of struggle.  Right now I just feel like i'm sitting in the back of of a dark cave somewhere and there are bats screaming in my ears all around me.  It's hard to see the beauty there, because it's chaos.  


I hope everyone is doing well.  I love you guys.
I wish my head would just start thinking clearly.  It's too hard trying to be rational about emotions.  It's gotta be like god's cruel joke or something.

love. You are a work of art.

I don't think I have ever had as much emotional related sickness and stress as I have had this week.  I was dry heaving again this morning.  I have been so mixed up inside.  Fortunately I have some really amazing, understanding, and supportive friends.  I'm exhausted and i have to work at 3:30am so i'm going to get some shut eye.  I hope everyone is doing well.
I'm better today then i was yesterday.  Still though I can't help worrying.  I hope that it gets easier with each day.  My stomach has been twisting in knots.  I just want things to be ok.
I don't know what is going on inside of me anymore.  It's been one day and I already miss you.

BRIGHT EYES LYRICS

"Method Acting"

There is no beginning to the story. A bookshelf sinks into the sand
and a language learned and forgot, in turn, is studied once again.
It's a shocking bit of footage viewed from a shitty TV screen.
You can squint through snowy static to make out the meaning.
Just keep on stretching the antennae, hoping that it will come clear.
We need some reception, a higher message, just tell us what to fear.
Because I don't know what tomorrow brings. It is alive with such possibilities.
All I know is I feel better when I sing. Burdens are lifted from me, that is my voice rising!
So Michael, please keep the tape rolling. Boys keep strumming those guitars.
We need a record of our failures. We must document out love.
I have sat too long in my silence. I have grown too old in my pain.
To shed this skin, be born again, it starts with an ending.
So thank you friends for the time we shared. My love stays with you like sunlight and air.
Oh how I truly wish I could keep hanging around here but my joy is covering me.
Soon, I will disappear.
It's not a movie, no private screening. This method acting, well, I call that living.
It's like a fountain, a door has been opened. We have a problem with no solution
but to love and to be loved.
So, I've made peace with the falling leaves. I see their same fate in my own body.
But I won't be afraid when I am awoken from this dream and returned to that
which gave birth to me. And the story goes on and on and on and on...

Well I only have two more weekends here at Ferris before graduation.  The weather has been amazing.  It is 76 out today.  Yesterday it was in the 70's also.  Tim, Jared, and I had been planning a canoe trip all week.  Unfortunately when we called the canoe rental place yesterday we found out that to rent a canoe it cost like 42 bucks for the three of us.  Also by the time we called they had already but their final boats in for the day.  So we were all bummed out.  We were determined to go on the river though so we went to the pawn shop to see if they were selling any canoes.  We didn't have any luck there so we went to meijer.  We found an inflatable three person boat for 29 dollars and a pump for 10.  We then noticed that the weight capacity for the boat was 350lbs.  Apparently it's only a three person boat if you are in Kenya lol.  Anyways we decided to give it a whirl.  Jared and I hopped in the boat and Timmy decided to get in the water and hold onto the side of the boat.  I think he is absolutely nuts because the water is freezing right now. He stayed in the water the whole time we were floating, which was for about 2 hours. It was really relaxing and fun floating down the Muskegon with my two best friends from college.  It is a memory that I hope I never forget.  There was a moment when I looked at them and I realized that I'm really going to miss them next year.  It was kind of hard not to cry but I held it in.  I think that it's really important for me to hang out with them as much as possible for these last few weeks because I know it will never be like this again. When I look back on my college years someday I hope that my thoughts are filled with memories like these.  I know that I will never be able to forget Jared, and Tim.  They truly are unique individuals.  Befriending them has been one of the best things to happen to me in college.  I know that more than any other part of college I will miss them.

Well it only took me five years but it is finally happening.  I am set to walk in my graduation commencements on Saturday may 7th.  I knew this day would come for sometime but now I can't believe it's actually here.  I feel like I am on a merry-go-round everything is happening so fast.  I guess it really hit me the other day when I had to go to the grad fair to pick up my cap and gown and cords.  I am so excited and yet at the same time I'm scared shitless.  After this is real life and I just don't feel like I am responsible enough to be completely independent.  It's like I'm standing on the edge of the diving board over the deep end wondering what will happen when I dive in.  Maybe I will swim (god I hope I swim) and maybe I will drowned at the bottom and never make it to the surface.  I remember when I was a little girl.  I didn't know how to swim so my dad decided to throw me in the middle of the deep end by myself.  I kicked my legs and arms franticly.  I was terrified.  I was swallowing and choking on water, but some how I made it to the edge.  Of course when I made it to the edge my dad decided to pick me up and toss me back in the deep end again (that bastard).  Each time he threw me back in the deep it got a bit easier to get back over to the edge.  Eventually I learned how to swim.  I guess this experience has taught me that a person doesn't really know what he/she is capable of until they are put to the test and that with each test the challenges will get a bit easier.  Still uncertainty is frightening.  I just hope that when I dive in I don't have to choke up too much water but I am definitely excited about learning how to swim again.

Yesterday I had a dream that i was babysitting my professor's duck.  The funny thing is my professor doesn't really have a duck so i don't know where i conjured that up from.  The ducks name was Condit (Condit is the name of the author of a journal article i just read).  Anyways somehow this duck got loose from my hands and ended up in the middle of traffic.  So i ran out into the street to try to save him.  I had to dodge cars left and right because they were all about to hit me.  Then all the cars started smashing into one another.  They created this circle around condit the duck.  The last thing I remember I was standing in the middle of all these crashed cars with the duck in my arms.  Condit was safe and then i woke up.

Well it is spring break so I'm in Sunny Scottsdale Arizona as usual.  It was kind of chilly today for Arizona but seeing as how it was 9 degrees on my way to the Detroit airport the other day 65 degrees seems pretty hot right now.  But don't feel too bad for me, it is supposed to get warmer soon (haha).  Sorry I just couldn't resist.  Even though I am enjoying myself here I miss all my wonderful friends in Michigan.  I hope your warm hearts are keeping you toasty.  (Speaking of toasty aren't Quizno's subs the best Mmm Toasty!!)  Sorry for the randomness I just love Quizno's. Anyways my boyfriend and I are spending nice quality time together which is awesome, but sucks at the same time.  It seems the more time I spend with him the harder it gets to leave him.  I can't wait until this distance between us no longer exists.  Then we can get on with our lives and we can finally really start to get to know each other extensively.  Don't get me wrong though even though the distance sucks it is still really worth it.  It is so hard to find someone who is honest, selfless, and pure in this world.  I found someone like that and if these are the struggles I have to go through to keep him then so be it.  I listen to all my roommate's stories of all her failed relationships, and I hear about all the losers she encounters.  If I were her I probably would have turned gay by now.  I know that I am blessed to have such an amazing man in my life so I am going to do everything I can to keep him around.
Happy Birthday Manfred.  It is still your B Day in Arizona

I'm in Arizona until Monday with my lil sis and her boyfriend.  Unfortunately it has been raining a lot but hey lets face it anything is better then Michigan right now.  We just got out of the hot tub and now we are about to start a fire pit outside and play some molly molly moose.  Let the night of drinking commence.  I hope everyone else is having as much fun as we are.

Yesterday I went to see the band Love Drug in Grand Rapids with Frisbee Tim.  It was awesome.  That band is amazing.  Unfortunately the emo kids suck.  No one really seemed to get into the music.  I mean I know you can't exactly head bang or anything but they could show some enthusiasm.  I will say one thing good thing about the crowed.  I didn't have to worry about getting hit in the head by a beer can like I would at a rock show.  The music was great and I guess that is all that really matters.  Small shows are defiantly the best.

So as I was describing in my last post this week just didn't seem to start off right.  I had this feeling in me that it wasn't going to be a great week since Sunday.  On the bright side I did well on the preso that I was worried about.  So I started to think maybe things were going to turn around for the week then I got in my car to go to my feminist class on Tues and I couldn't get the key to turn in my ignition.  I had to call my friend Jared to give me a ride to my class, which I arrived late for.  My professor ended up giving me a ride home after class.  So today I got to start my birthday off by having my car towed across the street to the ford dealership.  They had to replace my ignition cylinder it cost me 150 bucks which is the amount of my whole paycheck.  Even though that was a drag I was trying to keep my chin up.  I had a lot of nice friends to help me out.  I had a lot of people call or im me wishing me a happy birthday.  So I was trying to be optimistic.  I spent most of my day studying for my psyc test which is tomorrow.  It was ok because I knew that tonight I would be at big boy with my friends having my annual hot fudge cake and ice cream treat.  It is the one time of the year where I allow myself to eat this super fattening desert that I love, without feeling guilty.  So as you might imagine I have been looking forward to this for a very long time.  So I ordered just a little bit to eat for dinner because I had to save room for my desert.  When it came time to order desert I was salivating because I was looking at the picture of my hot fudge cake on the menu.  Then waiter came over to our table and told us the dreadful news.  WE DON"T HAVE ANY HOT FUDGE CAKE TONIGHT!!!! It was a shot to the heart. I instantly bowed my head in disappointment.  Then all my friends began to laugh because they new what kind of day I was having, and that I have been talking about the hot fudge cake forever.  Then I just started to laugh and I told the waiter that this was the worst birthday ever.  LMAO then he said "oh it's your birthday"?  He informed me that because it was my B day I would get desert free.  That would have been great news for me except my friend Tim was already paying for my meal so I guess that was good news for him.  I settled with the apple ice cream puff.  It was alright but it just wasn't the same as the hot fudge cake.  Now I will spend the remainder of my birthday studying for my psycho test blah.

There were a few highlights today though.  I had family and friends all wishing the best for me.  Even if my day didn't turn out so well, I guess it could be a lot worse.  I had the company of my friends at dinner, and a lot of really special people took time out of their day to think of me.  So thank you all for that.  

P.S. Next year I am calling ahead to make sure they have hot fudge cake
